The paper discusses adversarial attacks on machine learning models, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories of computer science. The most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper proposes a real-time adversarial attack scheme for machine learning models. The second likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), as the paper discusses the vulnerability of machine learning algorithms to adversarial attacks. The third likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), as adversarial attacks on image recognition models have been extensively studied in this field. The fourth likely category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), as the paper discusses the limitations of current adversarial attack methods on machine learning models. The fifth likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), as the paper proposes a real-time attack scheme for machine learning models with streaming inputs, which is relevant to networked systems.
